---
name: feedback_never_suggest_https
description: Never suggest downgrading from SSH to HTTPS for git operations
type: feedback
---

Never suggest using HTTPS as an alternative to SSH for git
operations. Do not suggest security downgrades of any kind.

**Why:** Edwin considers HTTPS a lesser security option. Suggesting
it as a workaround for SSH issues is unacceptable.

**How to apply:** When SSH to GitHub times out, suggest retrying
or investigating the network issue. Never offer HTTPS as a
fallback.
